<P><A name=3Dsecuring-oss-2008><FONT size=3D+2><B>Securing Open Source =
Software=20
(OSS)</B></FONT></A></P>
<P></P>
<P>I've just posted my <A=20
href=3D"http://www.dwheeler.com/essays/securing-oss.pdf">presentation =
titled=20
"Securing Open Source Software (OSS or FLOSS)</A>, which is to be =
presented at=20
the <A href=3D"http://www.bowheadevents.com/swaforum2008/index.cfm">8th=20
Semi-Annual Software Assurance Forum, May 6-8, 2008, Sheraton Premiere, =
Tyson's=20
Corner in Vienna, Virginia.</A> In it, I discuss how to improve the =
security of=20
an OSS component by modifying its environment, as well as securing the =
OSS=20
component itself (by selecting a secure component, building a secure =
component=20
from scratch, or modifying an existing component). I include a number of =

examples; they're necessarily incomplete, but I hope it will help people =
who are=20
developing or deploying systems. (Here is <A=20
href=3D"http://www.dwheeler.com/essays/securing-oss.odp">"Securing Open =
Source=20
Software (OSS or FLOSS)" in OpenDocument format</A>.) Enjoy! </P>
